In 1889 the part of the parish of Latchford within the borough 
    of Warrington became part of Lancashire. In 1894 the part remaining in Cheshire 
    became the separate parish of Latchford Without, so that thereafter Latchford 
    was wholly in Lancashire. The parish was abolished 30.9.1898 and added to the parish of Warrington. See also Table 2, notes (a) and (d).

Created 1894 from the rural part of the parish of Latchford. See 
    also Table 2, note (c).

Created 1894 out of the parish of Warrington. Abolished 9.11.1896 
    and added to the parish of Warrington.
